ENTRY            D1086   20260224   20260508   20260508       D151
SUBENT        D1086001   20260224   20260508   20260508       D151
BIB                 10         25
TITLE      Energy dependence of p+232Th fission mass
            distributions: mass-asymmetric standard I and
            standard II modes, and multichance fission
AUTHOR     (A.C.Berriman, D.J.Hinde, D.Y.Jeung, M.Dasgupta,
            H.Haba, T.Tanaka, K.Banerjee, T.Banerjee, L.T.Bezzina,
            J.Buete, K.J.Cook, S.Parker-Steele, C.Sengupta,
            C.Simenel, E.C.Simpson, M.A.Stoyer,
            B.M.A.Swinton-Bland, E.Williams)
INSTITUTE  (3AULCBR,2JPNIPC,1USAMSU,1USALRL)
REFERENCE  (J,PR/C,105,064614,2022)
REL-REF    (O,31853001,A.C.Berriman+,J,PR/C,105,064614,2022)
           Spontaneous fission of 248Cm compiled separately.
FACILITY   (VDGT,3AULCBR) 14UD tandem accelerator
SAMPLE     The 232Th target (~65 ug/cm2 areal density) was vacuum
            deposited onto an Al backing of ~60 ug/cm2.
DETECTOR   (MWPC) Fission fragments were detected by CUBE
            spectrometer with two (DC) or three (pulsed beam
            measurements) with active area up to (279 x 357 mm),
            positioned 180 or 195 mm from the target.
           (SI) Silicon monitor detectors located at 22.5 degree
            scattering angle.
STATUS     No data have been received from the author despite
            several requests; the first request was sent to
            D.Hinde on 12th October 2023.
HISTORY    (20260224C) VT
ENDBIB              25
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           28
